  "translations": {
    "en": "When the news of his death reached Uthman, he came and stood at his grave and said: \"May Allah bless you with mercy; you were good, even though you were (my opponent).\" He praised him well. Al-Zubair said to him: \"You will know me after death when you lament me, while during my lifetime you did not provide me my sustenance.\" He said: \"O Zubair, you say this? Do you think I like to see such a companion of Muhammad, peace be upon him and his progeny, die while he is resentful against me?!\"",
